</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="719" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="11.[1369,2576,2290,3150]" pageId="11" pageNumber="719">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1372,1505,2645,2678]" pageId="11" pageNumber="719">Breeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but female Secretive Dwarf Squirrels have three pairs of teats, two inguinal and one post-axillary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="719" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="11.[1369,2576,2290,3150]" pageId="11" pageNumber="719">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1369,1608,2723,2756]" pageId="11" pageNumber="719">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but the Secretive Dwarf Squirrel is diurnal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
