</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="719" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="11.[1369,2576,2290,3150]" pageId="11" pageNumber="719">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1372,1719,2885,2914]" pageId="11" pageNumber="719">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Secretive Dwarf Squirrel is only known by the 30 original specimens collected in 1932 by G. Heinrich and by one additional specimen collected in the 1950s, all in the Mekongga Mountains in SE Sulawesi, a mountain range that has not been surveyed since the species’ description in 1958. The habitat ofthis area is considered to be relatively intact, but new surveys are needed to confirm this.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
